<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw">1806</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">July</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">-ed.  They dress nearly the same as the Mandanes, abateing their hair which they adjust differently.  They wear it trailling on the ground plaited in small tresses in which they put small pieces of gum and which they adorn with patches of red and white clay by way of paint.  They take pride in Exposing their nudities &#8212; and are as I am informed partial to unnatural connections<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  They prefer Young men to young women and have many <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Berdashes</span> who make it their business to satisfy their abominable desires<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The men are always ready to supply strangers with bed fellows of their own choosing from among their wives and are proud when a friend can be accomodated with one who is well provided with a <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Contrivant</span> upon the nature of this extraordinary appendage I cannot say much.  It is produced by a filthy habit of the men who handle and stretch that part to the length of several inches when the girls are still in their teens &#8212; whether this is the cause depends upon report but that the women have such ornaments I can positively affirm.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">These people like their neighbours wash themselves morning and evening wallowing in clay</p>
